    <example class="- topic/example " id="example" otherprops="examples" xtrc="example:1;44:49" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/colspec.dita"><title class="- topic/title " xtrc="title:3;44:56" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/colspec.dita">Example</title><p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:2;44:74" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/colspec.dita">See <xref class="- topic/xref " href="table.dita" xtrc="xref:4;44:103" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/colspec.dita" type="reference"><?ditaot gentext?>table<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">The <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:2;6:28" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/table.dita">table</xmlelement> element organizes arbitrarily complex relationships of     tabular information. This standard table markup allows column or row spanning and table captions     or descriptions. An optional title allowed inside the <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:3;8:71" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/table.dita">table</xmlelement> element     provides a caption to describe the table.</desc></xref>.</p></example>
